As many as 285 appeals had been received this year, Minister for Education P.K. Abdu Rabb said.This was one-fourth the number of appeals received during the previous festivals. The number did not include the appeals allowed by the court, he said.Mr. Rabb said steps had been taken to bring down the number of complaints at festivals. Inquiry had been conducted into specific complaints. Steps were also being planned in this regard for next yearâ€™s festival.On complaints about the judging process at school festivals held across the State, he said people against whom complaints had been raised had not been invited to judge events this year.